te the constitutional, legal, social and political background of the speech. The book is of the highest interest to scholars and students of the Attic Orators, Athenian society, daily life, women and gender relations, law, constitution, institutions, religion and culture.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aProstituteszGreecezAthens. 0aProstitutionzGreecezAthens. 0aSpeeches, addresses, etc., Greek. 4aDemosthenes / In Neaeram. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 1990 - 1999z9783110636116oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION 2: BEST OF CLASSICAL STUDIES TITLES IN ENGLISHz9783110305708oZDB-23-DBB08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION 2: BEST OF CLASSICAL STUDIESz9783110305609oZDB-23-DBA0 cprintz978311016390240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311080986240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110809862423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110809862/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DBA  aZDB-23-DBB  aZDB-23-GCNc1990d1999